channel.title: Router problems
channel.description:
I have a Belkin wireless router DF7320-4 or something like that.
I tried to log into the router but I kept getting a failed login screen even though I'm the administrator.
I want to get this thing working so I can up my server and hire a coder and what not.
Any ideas on whats wrong?

item.title: Router problems
item.dc:creator: @Y0_J0k3r Y0_J0k3r
item.description:
@Y0_J0k3r wrote:

Enter your ip into the address bar…
Then for most routers the username is blank and the password is Admin…
If you changed it and cant remember what you have put then hold down the
reset button which is on the back of the actual router.
This is a problem that I had but I got it fixed. Hope this helped.
